The paper deals with distributed graph algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The main problem studied in the paper is weak splitting, which is a graph coloring problem, and thus it can also be categorized under Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses related problems such as coloring nodes with multiple colors and limiting the number of neighbors of each color, which can be categorized under Networked Information Systems (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
